 u.s. intelligence picked up more credible and
 imminent terrorist threats. so now all american troops in
 the persian gulf are at the highest state of alert --
 threat con delta. as the "uss cole" prepares
 to come home -- 20 miles out to sea,
 the crippled "cole" is loaded onto the heavy lift ship, "blue
 marlin." in this navy satellite video,
 the marlin actually submerges. tugs push the cole into position
 over the deck, and the marlin rises to lift the 8,000 ton
 warship out of the water. the cole will take the long way
 home, around the southern tip of africa on its way to norfolk,
 avoiding the shorter route through the suez canal
 because of ongoing terrorist threats.
